  • Method Details

    • cancelPublication

      public PublishApi.CancelPublicationAdapter cancelPublication(String hrn, String publicationId, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Cancels a publication if it has not yet been submitted. Will fail if attempting to cancel a submitted publication. This allows the specified publication to be abandoned. See Data API Developer&rsquo;s Guide in the Documentation section for publication states diagram and all possible publication states transitions.

      Path: /publications/{publicationId}

      Method: DELETE

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : (Publication was cancelled successfully.)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized.)

      code 403 : (Forbidden.)

      code 404 : (Publication not found.)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      publicationId - The ID of the publication to cancel.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters and contain only alphanumeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • getPublication

      public PublishApi.GetPublicationAdapter getPublication(String hrn, String publicationId, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Returns the details of the specified publication. Publication can be in one of these states: Initialized, Submitted, Cancelled, Failed, Succeeded, Expired. See Data API Developer&rsquo;s Guide in the Documentation section for the publication state diagram.

      Path: /publications/{publicationId}

      Method: GET

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : Publication (The publication details.)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized.)

      code 403 : (Forbidden.)

      code 404 : (Publication not found.)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      publicationId - The ID of the publication to retrieve.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters and contain only alphanumeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • initPublication

      public PublishApi.InitPublicationAdapter initPublication(String hrn, com.here.platform.data.client.base.generated.scaladsl.model.publish.Publication body, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Initializes a new publication for publishing metadata. Determines the publication type based on the provided layer IDs. A publication can only consist of layer IDs that have the same layer type. For example, you can have a publication for multiple layers of type versioned, but you cannot have a single publication that publishes to both versioned and volatile layers. In addition, you may only have one versioned publication in process at a time. The body field versionDependencies is optional and is used for versioned layers to declare version dependencies.

      Path: /publications

      Method: POST

      Expected answers:

      code 200 : Publication (New publication created.) Headers : Location - The location of the newly created publication.

      code 400 : (Bad request, it is impossible to publish to all the requested layers in one single publication.)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized.)

      code 403 : (Forbidden.)

      code 409 : (Conflict with an another active publication.)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      body - Fields to initialize a publication.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters, contain only alpha/numeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • submitPublication

      public PublishApi.SubmitPublicationAdapter submitPublication(String hrn, String publicationId, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Submits the publication and initiates post processing if necessary. Publication state becomes Submitted directly after submission and Succeeded after successful processing. See Data API Developer&rsquo;s Guide in the Documentation section for complete publication states diagram.

      Path: /publications/{publicationId}

      Method: PUT

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : (Publication was submitted successfully.)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized.)

      code 403 : (Forbidden.)

      code 404 : (Publication not found.)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      publicationId - ID of publication to submit.
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters and contain only alphanumeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.

    • uploadPartitions

      public PublishApi.UploadPartitionsAdapter uploadPartitions(String hrn, String layerId, String publicationId, com.here.platform.data.client.base.generated.scaladsl.model.publish.PublishPartitions body, Optional<String> billingTag)
      Upload partitions to the given layer. Dependending on the publication type, post processing may be required before the partitions are published. For better performance batch your partitions (e.g. 10000 per request), rather than uploading them individually.

      Path: /layers/{layerId}/publications/{publicationId}/partitions

      Method: POST

      Expected answers:

      code 204 : (Partitions successfully submitted.)

      code 400 : (Bad request, trying to publish partitions with fields not applicable or mandatory fields missing, given the layer type.)

      code 401 : (Unauthorized.)

      code 403 : (Forbidden.)

      code 404 : (Publication not found.)

      Parameters:
      hrn - The HERE Resource Name (HRN) of the catalog.
      layerId - The ID of the layer to publish to.
      publicationId - The ID of publication to publish to.
      body - Publication partitions. fields
      billingTag - Billing Tag is an optional free-form tag which is used for grouping billing records together. If supplied, it must be between 4 - 16 characters and contain only alphanumeric ASCII characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Grouping billing records by billing tag will be available in future releases.
